The paper deals with 3D shape retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and computer graphics (GR) techniques. The use of GPU acceleration and inverted files suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (MM) and information retrieval (IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of the proposed method, which may also make it relevant to the data structures (DS) sub-category.
